Comrade de Blasio is at it again. 
Now he is encouraging NYC schools to ‘resist’ ICE agents. 
From Townhall: googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1481811813211-0'); }); 
At a press conference in front of New York’s Tweed Courthouse on Tuesday, Mayor Bill de Blasio laid out the city’s plans to resist U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement agents in the Trump era. googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1464204305408-0'); }); 
There are “deep fears and concerns” among immigrant families after President Trump announced new ICE protocols that give agents more freedom to hold illegal immigration raids, the mayor noted. googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1481811813211-1'); }); 
Um, if you entered the country illegally, maybe you should have fear of being caught? 
“We think it’s crucial to fight for all New Yorkers and to help immigrant New Yorkers to know their rights,” De Blasio said. “This is your city. Your city will stand by you.” 
De Blasio detailed a few ways the city plans to assuage parents’ fears and resist ICE. His office, he said, will be instructing school employees to understand what to do in which ICE agents appear at a school. The agents, he said, will be kept outside the school buildings and schools will not share information with them unless required by the law. 
No, it’s not “your city” and that’s sort of the point. googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1481811813211-2'); }); 
But even beyond the school, the city is going to spend taxpayer dollars helping counsel people how to resist ICE and to resist deportation. googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1448050117784-4'); }); googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1464204305408-1'); }); 
The city will also facilitate workshops for parents to get questions answered about their rights in general and how they can get help. They have planned over 100 Know Your Rights workshops in boroughs throughout the city which will inform families where they can seek legal assistance, and free immigration services if they are facing the threat of deportation. googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1481811813211-3'); }); 
He’s also cool with shielding drunk drivers from ICE enforcement as well. 
As a practical matter, the Mayor is posturing. 
Because ICE wouldn’t be going in the schools without warrants in any event and if they had them, the schools couldn’t stop them. 
So the Mayor is simply posturing to be anti-Trump and burnish up his progressive bona fides for his anticipated run for president in 2020. 
But he’s using the money of the people of the city of New York to do it. googletag.cmd.push(function() { googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1481811813211-4'); });
